# Receivable workflows

Canonical source: `src/domain/receivable/transitions.ts` + `docs/notes/2026-05-19_platform-auth-rbac-receivable-v1.md`.

## Status machine

```
                  ┌──── risk_analyst / risk_analyst_agent ────►  rejected  (terminal)
under_review ─────┤
                  └──── risk_analyst / risk_analyst_agent ────►  offer
                                                                      │
                                                              payer ──►  confirmed
                                                                              │
                                                           system only ──►  processing
                                                                              │
                                                           system only ──►  completed  (terminal)
```

- **First stored status is `under_review`** — there is no `created` status in DB; `created_at` is metadata only.
- `rejected` and `completed` are terminal; no transitions out.
- `processing` and `completed` are **system-only** — no JWT user may trigger them.

## RBAC transition matrix

| From | To | Who |
|------|----|-----|
| *(POST /v1/receivables)* | `under_review` | `seller` (creates the row) |
| `under_review` | `offer` | `risk_analyst` or `risk_analyst_agent` |
| `under_review` | `rejected` | `risk_analyst` or `risk_analyst_agent` |
| `offer` | `confirmed` | `payer` bound to `payer_user_id` on the row |
| `confirmed` | `processing` | **system** (`X-Dupply-Api-Key` only) |
| `processing` | `completed` | **system** (`X-Dupply-Api-Key` only) |

## Domain guard — always use it

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — enforce in one place
assertReceivableTransition(from, to, actor);

// ❌ BAD — inline role checks in HTTP handlers
if (req.user.role !== 'risk_analyst') throw ...
```

`assertReceivableTransition` lives in `src/domain/receivable/transitions.ts`. All mutating routes **must** call it. Do not duplicate logic in route handlers.

## Actor shape

```typescript
type TransitionActor =
  | { kind: "system" }             // X-Dupply-Api-Key callers
  | { kind: "user"; role: string } // JWT callers
```

## Roles

```
seller            — creates receivables; no lifecycle transitions after that
payer             — confirms discount; bound to receivable.payer_user_id
risk_analyst      — human review
risk_analyst_agent — automation (n8n/agent); same privilege as risk_analyst for receivables
admin             — platform ops; specific route ACL TBD
```

## Key invariants

- `seller` and `payer` are **always different identities** on the same receivable.
- `proposedValue` is required when `risk_analyst` moves to `offer`; must be present in DB.
- `processing` / `completed` cannot be triggered by any authenticated user — internal route only (`POST /v1/internal/receivables/:id/advance-settlement`).
- Timestamps: `created_at_ms` is immutable (set on insert); `updated_at_ms` is bumped on every transition.

## Adding new transitions

1. Update `RECEIVABLE_STATUS` constant in `transitions.ts`.
2. Add the case inside `assertReceivableTransition`.
3. Write unit tests in `tests/domain/receivable/transitions.test.ts` covering allowed actor and disallowed actors.
4. Update `docs/notes/2026-05-19_platform-auth-rbac-receivable-v1.md` if the rule is normative.
